      "content": "The core of this debate lies in balancing individual conscience with the state's duty to enforce uniform laws. While religious freedom is a fundamental right, granting broad exemptions to government mandates can erode the legal framework that ensures equal treatment for all citizens. A secular state relies on consistent rules to maintain social order and prevent the fragmentation of public policy. Therefore, the rule of law should generally take precedence over religious preferences to preserve the integrity of the legal system.",
